            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 18-F radioactive beam, ionized to 2+ state."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Proton from the H-2(F-18,p+a)N-15 are",
                "detected in LAMP in coincidence with alpha-particle or",
                "N-15 in LEDA. Both type of coincidences can be",
                "separated using the TOF information in LEDA, but since",
                "the p-alpha coincidences represented only 7% of the",
                "total coincidence events, only the p-N-15 coincidences",
                "were analyzed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " DWBA calculations were performed with the",
                "FRESCO code in finite-range."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "POT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Spectroscopic factors for the F-19 levels analyzed in",
                " DWBA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The products of the D(F-18,p)F-19",
                "reaction were detected using the multi-strip silicon",
                "detector LEDA.",
                "Two configurations named LEDA and LAMP were used. These",
                "detectors are composed of 8 and 6 sectors, respectively",
                "each divided into 16 radial strips. The protons from",
                "the D(F-18,p)F-19 reaction were detected in LAMP,",
                "positioned 8.7-cm upstream from the target.",
                "The other detector, LEDA, is made up of eight sectors",
                "forming a disk positioned 40-cm downstream from the",
                "target and is used for background reduction and",
                "normalization."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
